cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing an efficient machine learning algorithm for tackling massive data challenges. The paper focuses on classification and uses polynomial kernels and an ADMM algorithm to achieve scalability and storage efficiency. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper deals with classification and optimization. Additionally, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories since the paper discusses machine learning algorithms.
